.TH GUIX "1" "January 2026" "GNU" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
guix \- manual page for guix graph (GNU Guix) 1.5.0rc1.47-fc2f5a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B guix
\fI\,graph PACKAGE\/\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Emit a representation of the dependency graph of PACKAGE...
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-backend\fR=\fI\,TYPE\/\fR
produce a graph with the given backend TYPE
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-backends\fR
list the available graph backends
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-type\fR=\fI\,TYPE\/\fR
represent nodes of the given TYPE
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-types\fR
list the available graph types
.TP
\fB\-M\fR, \fB\-\-max\-depth\fR=\fI\,DEPTH\/\fR
limit to nodes within distance DEPTH
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR
display the shortest path between the given nodes
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-expression\fR=\fI\,EXPR\/\fR
consider the package EXPR evaluates to
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-load\-path\fR=\fI\,DIR\/\fR
prepend DIR to the package module search path
.TP
\fB\-\-help\-transform\fR
list package transformation options not shown here
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
display version information and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-systems\fR
list available systems
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-system\fR=\fI\,SYSTEM\/\fR
attempt to build for SYSTEM\-\-e.g., "i686\-linux"
